 Houck telescope, a fork mounted cassegrain reflector telescope whose primary
 mirror is 25 inches (0.635 meters) in diameter.
 It has a f/13.5 lens, with a native plate scale of 24 arcsec/mm.
 Photon detection was performed using an Andor iDus 440 CCD, which sports
 a coated e2v CCD 42-10 BV sensor.
